How the Wheel Works:

Start: Begin with cash or existing shares
Sell OTM Cash-Secured Puts (CSP): Sell puts below the current stock price to collect premium
If CSP expires worthless: Keep the premium and repeat step 2
If CSP is assigned: You acquire shares at the strike price
Sell OTM Covered Calls (CC): Once you have shares, sell calls above the current price
If CC expires worthless: Keep the premium and repeat step 5
If CC is assigned: Your shares are sold at the strike price, and you return to step 2
This creates a continuous cycle of generating income while potentially accumulating or managing stock positions.
