When your covered call is assigned and shares are sold:

Collect the strike price - You've sold at a profit (strike > your cost basis ideally)
Keep the premium - This is yours regardless
Use cash to sell puts - Start the wheel by selling cash-secured puts
Target entry point - Sell puts at a strike where you'd happily buy back in
Repeat the cycle - Get assigned? Sell covered calls. Expire worthless? Sell more puts.
The Key Insight: Being "called away" isn't losing - it's taking profits and resetting for the next opportunity. The wheel keeps your capital working whether you hold shares or cash.

